# Branching & PR Strategy

## Branch Hierarchy

| Branch | Purpose | Merges Into |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| `main` | Production-ready | — |
| `front-main` | Frontend integration staging | `main` |
| `back-main` | Backend integration staging | `main` |
| `front-main-[feature]` | Frontend feature work | `front-main` |
| `back-main-[feature]` | Backend feature work | `back-main` |
| `integration-[feature]` | Cross-team features | `main` |
| `hotfix-[issue]` | Critical production fixes | `main` |

## Branch Naming

Use `<team>-main-<feature-name>` in lowercase kebab-case. Be descriptive and include the domain area.

```
front-main-task-board
back-main-task-crud-api
```

## PR Guidelines

- PRs target team integration branches (`front-main` or `back-main`), not `main` directly
- Keep PRs small: aim for <500 lines changed
- Require 1 approval for team branches, 2 approvals for `main`
- Squash merge for clean history
- All CI checks must pass

## Cross-Team Features

1. Agree on the contract first — shared DTOs and ports in `src/core/[feature]/application/`
2. Backend builds against the contract, frontend builds with mock data
3. Both merge independently into team branches
4. Integration tests verify compatibility before merging to `main`
